The White House said a tax increaseis not needed to reduce the federal budget deficit.    "We think that's certainly unnecessary. We are opposed totax increases," spokesman Marlin Fitzwater said.    House Speaker Jim Wright told Budget Committee DemocratsWednesday he would fight for a tax increase this year to reducethe deficit.    Fitzwater said the administration believed its budget wouldshow the way to get the deficit down without a tax rise "andthat's our course." Reuter&#3;